# Working Principles

- Clarify any material ambiguity before acting.
- Prefer the simplest viable solution.
- Do not invent requirements, APIs, files, or behavior.
- Use the active plan as the working contract for non-trivial work.
- Announce non-trivial actions before making them.
- Keep changes within the approved scope.
- Favor root-cause fixes over surface patches.
- Do not bypass safeguards silently.
